[eisuser@eisuatsftp01 Denny]$ podman kube play --help
Play a pod or volume based on Kubernetes YAML

Description:
  Reads in a structured file of Kubernetes YAML.

  Creates pods or volumes based on the Kubernetes kind described in the YAML. Supported kinds are Pods, Deployments, DaemonSets, Jobs, and PersistentVolumeClaims.

Usage:
  podman kube play [options] KUBEFILE|-

Examples:
  podman kube play nginx.yml
  cat nginx.yml | podman kube play -
  podman kube play --creds user:password --seccomp-profile-root /custom/path apache.yml
  podman kube play https://example.com/nginx.yml

Options:
      --annotation stringArray        Add annotations to pods (key=value)
      --authfile string               Path of the authentication file. Use REGISTRY_AUTH_FILE environment variable to override
      --build                         Build all images in a YAML (given Containerfiles exist)
      --cert-dir Pathname             Pathname of a directory containing TLS certificates and keys
      --configmap Pathname            Pathname of a YAML file containing a kubernetes configmap
      --context-dir string            Path to top level of context directory
      --creds Credentials             Credentials (USERNAME:PASSWORD) to use for authenticating to a registry
      --force                         Remove volumes as part of --down
      --ip ipSlice                    Static IP addresses to assign to the pods (default [])
      --log-driver string             Logging driver for the container (default "journald")
      --log-opt stringArray           Logging driver options
      --mac-address strings           Static MAC addresses to assign to the pods
      --network stringArray           Connect pod to network(s) or network mode
      --no-hostname                   Do not create /etc/hostname within the container, instead use the version from the image
      --no-hosts                      Do not create /etc/hosts within the pod's containers, instead use the version from the image
      --publish strings               Publish a container's port, or a range of ports, to the host
      --publish-all                   Whether to publish all ports defined in the K8S YAML file (containerPort, hostPort), if false only hostPort will be published
  -q, --quiet                         Suppress output information when pulling images
      --replace                       Delete and recreate pods defined in the YAML file
      --seccomp-profile-root string   Directory path for seccomp profiles (default "/var/lib/kubelet/seccomp")
      --start                         Start the pod after creating it (default true)
      --tls-verify                    Require HTTPS and verify certificates when contacting registries (default true)
      --userns string                 User namespace to use
  -w, --wait                          Clean up all objects created when a SIGTERM is received or pods exit

